I89. Definitions

I11For purposes of this Act [sections 2061 to 2170, 2171, and 2172 of this Appendix], the following definitions shall apply:

I79(1) Critical component

I12The term ``critical component'' includes such components, subsystems, systems, and related special tooling and test equipment essential to the production, repair, maintenance, or operation of weapon systems or other items of equipment identified by the President as being essential to the execution of the national security strategy of the United States. Components identified as critical by a National Security Assessment conducted pursuant to section 113(i) of title 10, United States Code, or by a Presidential determination as a result of a petition filed under section 232 of the Trade Expansion Act of 1962 [19 U.S.C. 1862] shall be designated as critical components for purposes of this Act [sections 2061 to 2170, 2171, and 2172 of this Appendix], unless the President determines that the designation is unwarranted.

I79(2) Critical infrastructure

I12The term ``critical infrastructure'' means any systems and assets, whether physical or cyber-based, so vital to the United States that the degradation or destruction of such systems and assets would have a debilitating impact on national security, including, but not limited to, national economic security and national public health or safety.

I79(3) Critical technology

I12The term ``critical technology'' includes any technology designated by the President to be essential to the national defense.

I79(4) Critical technology item

I12The term ``critical technology item'' means materials directly employing, derived from, or utilizing a critical technology.

I79(5) Defense contractor

I12The term ``defense contractor'' means any person who enters into a contract with the United States_

I13(A) to furnish materials, industrial resources, or a critical technology for the national defense; or

I13(B) to perform services for the national defense.

I79(6) Domestic industrial base

I12The term ``domestic industrial base'' means domestic sources which are providing, or which would be reasonably expected to provide, materials or services to meet national defense requirements during peacetime, national emergency, or war.

I79(7) Domestic source

I12The term ``domestic source'' means a business concern_

I13(A) that performs in the United States or Canada substantially all of the research and development, engineering, manufacturing, and production activities required of such business concern under a contract with the United States relating to a critical component or a critical technology item; and

I13(B) that procures from business concerns described in subparagraph (A) substantially all of any components and assemblies required under a contract with the United States relating to a critical component or critical technology item.

I79(8) Facilities

I12The term ``facilities'' includes all types of buildings, structures, or other improvements to real property (but excluding farms, churches or other places of worship, and private dwelling houses), and services relating to the use of any such building, structure, or other improvement.

I79(9) Foreign source

I12The term ``foreign source'' means a business entity other than a ``domestic source''.

I79(10) Guaranteeing agency

I12The term ``guaranteeing agency'' means a department or agency of the United States engaged in procurement for the national defense.

I79(11) Homeland security

I12The term ``homeland security'' includes efforts_

I13(A) to prevent terrorist attacks within the United States;

I13(B) to reduce the vulnerability of the United States to terrorism;

I13(C) to minimize damage from a terrorist attack in the United States; and

I13(D) to recover from a terrorist attack in the United States.

I79(12) Industrial resources

I12The term ``industrial resources'' means materials, services, processes, or manufacturing equipment (including the processes, technologies, and ancillary services for the use of such equipment) needed to establish or maintain an efficient and modern national defense industrial base.

I79(13) Materials

I12The term ``materials'' includes_

I13(A) any raw materials (including minerals, metals, and advanced processed materials), commodities, articles, components (including critical components), products, and items of supply; and

I13(B) any technical information or services ancillary to the use of any such materials, commodities, articles, components, products, or items.

I79(14) National defense

I12The term ``national defense'' means programs for military and energy production or construction, military or critical infrastructure assistance to any foreign nation, homeland security, stockpiling, space, and any directly related activity. Such term includes emergency preparedness activities conducted pursuant to title VI of The Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act [42 U.S.C. 5195 et seq.] and critical infrastructure protection and restoration.

I79(15) Person

I12The term ``person'' includes an individual, corporation, partnership, association, or any other organized group of persons, or legal successor or representative thereof, or any State or local government or agency thereof.

I79(16) Services

I12The term ``services'' includes any effort that is needed for or incidental to_

I13(A) the development, production, processing, distribution, delivery, or use of an industrial resource or a critical technology item;

I13(B) the construction of facilities;

I13(C) the movement of individuals and property by all modes of civil transportation; or

I13(D) other national defense programs and activities.

I79(17) Small business concern

I12The term ``small business concern'' means a business concern that meets the requirements of section 3(a) of the Small Business Act [15 U.S.C. 632(a)] and the regulations promulgated pursuant to that section, and includes such business concerns owned and controlled by socially and economically disadvantaged individuals or by women.

